div1.p: I certify that I served the within Warrant by arresting James Sheridan in the County of Walla Walla this 2nd day of May A. D. 1863
E. R. Whitman Sheriff of Walla Walla Co W.T.
Territory of Washington County of Walla Walla
In the United States, District Court 1st Judicial District
To the Sheriff or his deputy, in said County In the name of the United States, Greeting!

Whereas, at a term of said Court, began and held at the City of Walla Walla in the said County the Grand Jury of said county good andlawful men duly empanelled and sworn did upon their oaths present adn find that James Sheridan late of Walla Walla, W. J., did commit the crime of Petit Larceny

These are therefore to command you that your forthwith take the body of the said James Sheridan and have him brought before said court to be dealt with according to law, Hereof fail not but of this writ make due service and return.
By order of the Court Given under my hand and the seal of said Court this 1st day of April May A. D. 1863
